1. GRANT OF LICENSE
-------------------

Subject to your compliance with every term of this license, the copyright
holders grant you a non-exclusive, non-transferable, non-sublicensable,
revocable, royalty-free license to:

  (a) Download Mneme from official distribution channels published by the
      copyright holders (the GitHub release page at
      https://github.com/omanishay-cyber/mneme, the official package
      manifests, or the Hugging Face Hub mirror).
  (b) Install Mneme on devices that you own or control.
  (c) Use Mneme to index, recall, audit, and operate on source code that
      you own or have explicit permission to use, for personal, internal,
      educational, or non-commercial purposes.

This grant covers personal individual use AND internal use within an
organization for that organization's own engineering work, provided no fee
is charged or value is received specifically for access to or use of Mneme
itself (see RESTRICTIONS §2).


2. RESTRICTIONS — what you MAY NOT do
--------------------------------------

You may not, and may not permit any other person to:

  (a) REDISTRIBUTE Mneme or any portion of it, in original or modified form,
      to any third party. This includes but is not limited to: re-uploading
      to any package registry, hosting on any download mirror, sharing
      binaries by direct transfer, including Mneme inside another product
      that is then distributed, or making Mneme available as a service to
      anyone outside your own organization.

  (b) MODIFY, adapt, translate, port, or create derivative works based on
      Mneme. You may not change the source code, binaries, models, or any
      other component, even for personal use, except for the express
      purpose of submitting a contribution back to the official repository
      (in which case you assign copyright in that contribution to the
      copyright holders by submitting it).

  (c) REVERSE-ENGINEER, decompile, disassemble, or otherwise attempt to
      derive the source code or internal structure of any compiled binary
      shipped as part of Mneme, except to the extent such restriction is
      forbidden by applicable law.

  (d) RE-BRAND, RE-NAME, FORK, or release any product based on Mneme under
      any other name, codename, mark, or identifier. This restriction
      explicitly forbids creating "your own version of Mneme" and applies
      to the source code, binaries, design assets, documentation, and
      website content alike.

  (e) USE THE MNEME NAME, the codenames "Mneme Genesis" / "Mneme Echo" /
      etc., the Mneme logo, or any associated trademark or trade dress
      for any product, service, project, organization, or marketing
      purpose not authorized in writing by the copyright holders.

  (f) USE Mneme COMMERCIALLY in any way that involves charging a fee for
      access to or use of Mneme itself, building a paid product whose
      value depends materially on Mneme, or offering Mneme as part of a
      service for which a third party pays. Internal commercial use by
      an organization for its own engineering work on its own codebases
      is permitted under the GRANT (§1) and is not a "commercial use"
      restricted by this clause.

  (g) REMOVE, ALTER, or OBSCURE any copyright notice, trademark notice,
      author attribution, license terms, version identifier, or telemetry
      opt-in disclosure that ships with Mneme.

  (h) USE Mneme in any way that violates applicable law, infringes the
      rights of any third party, or operates outside the boundaries of
      this license.


