4. THIRD-PARTY COMPONENTS
-------------------------

Mneme bundles, links to, or downloads at install time various third-party
open-source components (Rust crates, Bun-installed npm packages, ONNX
runtime, GGUF models from BAAI / Qwen team / Microsoft, etc.). Each of
those components is licensed under its own terms — typically permissive
licenses such as Apache-2.0, MIT, BSD, or model-specific terms. Those
components are NOT covered by this Mneme Personal-Use License; their own
licenses govern. The list of third-party components and their licenses
is available in the source repository.

This license applies only to the parts of Mneme authored by the copyright
holders. It does not extend, override, or restrict the licenses of any
third-party component.


5. PRIVACY AND TELEMETRY
------------------------

Mneme is designed to run entirely on your local machine. The official
distribution does not transmit your source code, your queries, or your
recall data to any external service. The only network calls Mneme makes
on your behalf are: (a) downloading model files from the official Hugging
Face mirror or GitHub Releases at install time, (b) checking for updates
from the GitHub Releases API when you explicitly run `mneme self-update
--check-only` or its equivalent, and (c) any explicit network operation
you opt into (e.g. `mneme models install --from-url`).

If you modify Mneme to add network egress (which §2(b) forbids), you do
so entirely at your own risk and your modification is not Mneme.


